   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>25.5.1884 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49069">Hamburg</placeName> May 25 1884.</p>
            <p>Went to Haspergs<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="1152">Amanda</persName> und
                     <persName key="11239">Heinrich</persName>
               </note>. I started at halfpast ten a.m.. When I got
               there I found out that the races in <placeName key="49382">Bahrenfeld</placeName>
               were not to take place till four o&#x2019;clock. So I stopped in the garden with <persName key="72975">Heine</persName>
               <note type="reg">Hasperg</note> till 2. Then we drove
               away in the dogcart. <persName key="22971">Paul</persName>
               <note type="reg">Hasperg</note> driving and <persName key="72925">Belle</persName>
               <note type="reg">Hasperg</note> sitting next to him, I and <persName key="72975">Heine</persName>
               on the other seat. The races were very nice. <persName key="1155">Ward</persName> and
                  <persName key="1240">Dickens</persName> were beaten but <persName key="22971">Paul</persName> won two races. The prizes for them were a large horn and a
               champaign-icer. The dust was simply fearful on the way back and we drove at a fearful
               pace. We dined at 8. Totty <persName key="1326">Burke</persName> was there too and a
               woman with a huge red satin star on one side that looked like a decoration. We were
               twenty-three. <persName key="1327">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi> Ehnett</persName> proposed <persName>Paul&#x2019;s</persName> health.</p>
         </div>
